class Solution {
    public int repeatedStringMatch(String a, String b) {
        int count = 1;
        String repeatA = a;
        while (repeatA.length() < b.length()) {
            repeatA += a;
            count++;
        }
        if (repeatA.indexOf(b) != -1) return count;
        repeatA += a;
        if (repeatA.indexOf(b) != -1) return count + 1;
        return -1;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution repeats string a until its length is greater than or equal to the length of string b, then checks if b is a substring of the repeated a. If not, it repeats a one more time and checks again.

